I.	Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Bridge Point Northlake (Northlake Cold Storage) facility located at 555 Northwest Avenue in Northlake, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This 5-year, updated Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 
	Introduction;
	Bridge Point Northlake policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
	Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
	Hazard Assessment;
	Prevention Program;
	Five-Year Accident History;
	Emergency Response Plan; 
	Emergency Communications;
	Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
	Planned changes to improve safety; and
	Management Program

II.	Bridge Point Northlake Policies To Protect Health, Environment and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Bridge Point Northlake; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Bridge Point Northlake is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Bridge Point Northlake policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations. 

